title: Highest Account Ownership Among Older Adults
description: In 2021, the Netherlands achieved a 100% account ownership rate at financial institutions or with mobile-money-service providers among adults aged 25 and older, showcasing its advanced financial inclusion.

title: Lowest Exposure to PM2.5 Pollution
description: As of 2017, only 0.04% of the Dutch population was exposed to PM2.5 pollution levels exceeding the WHO's Interim Target-3, highlighting the country's effective environmental policies.

title: High Youth Employment Rate
description: In 2024, the employment to population ratio for Dutch youth aged 15-24 was 76.645%, indicating strong job opportunities for young people in the Netherlands.

title: Strong Female Labor Force Participation
description: The labor force participation rate for females aged 15-24 in the Netherlands reached 83.079% in 2024, reflecting gender inclusivity in the workforce.

title: Significant Foreign Direct Investment Outflows
description: In 2023, the Netherlands recorded a net outflow of foreign direct investment amounting to -$332.5 billion, indicating a substantial investment presence abroad.
